# Agent Process — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Read `AGENT_PROCESS.md` before starting any implementation task.

## Mandatory rules

- **P0/P1 work:** branch → implement → `make ci-local` → PR → notify human (no auto-merge)
- **P2 work:** branch → implement → `make ci-local` → PR → `gh pr merge --auto --squash`
- **P3 (docs only):** commit directly to main
- **Never skip** `make ci-local` before opening a PR
- **Never force-push** to main
- **Never merge** P0/P1 without human approval

## Branch naming

- Work orders: `wo/NNN-short-description`
- Hotfixes: `fix/short-description`

## Work Order pickup

Every WO spec has a `## Execution` section with:
- Branch name
- Risk tier
- PR title
- PM docs to update

Read it. Follow it exactly.
